kieker.diagnosis.domain

Class AbstractOperationCall<T extends AbstractOperationCall<T>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • kieker.diagnosis.domain.AbstractOperationCall<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The precise type of the children. This should usually be the implementing class itself.
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AggregatedDatabaseOperationCall, AggregatedOperationCall, DatabaseOperationCall, OperationCall, PreparedStatementCall

    public abstract class AbstractOperationCall<T extends AbstractOperationCall<T>>
extends java.lang.Object
    This is an abstract base for classes representing operation calls (also called executions) within this application. As it can has multiple children, an instance of this class can represent a whole call tree. This class implements the both methods equals(Object) and hashCode(), allowing to easily check whether two traces are equal and should be in the same equivalence class.
    Author:
    Nils Christian Ehmke, Christian Zirkelbach
